<br>
Uggmo - you are a raving idiot.<br>
<br>
Being late for an interview due to your irresponsibility is GROSSLY different - and you DAMN well know it.<br>
<br>
I in NO FASHION showed that drugs being illegal is worse than drugs being legalized.  I did not hardly BEGIN to speak on the bad things that happen to people on drugs.  I avoided this topic because that is not the point of this debate - AS I HAVE STATED ABOUT A HALF DOZEN TIMES.<br>
<br>
Being close minded is not necessarily a bad thing, either.  I'm rather close minded in my opinion on things such as rape and murder... damn, I guess that makes me wrong on those, too.<br>
<br>
I encourage the youth to make their own decisions, as well.  I, however, remember being a kid once.  Do you, Uggmo?  I remember the times I thought my parents were absolutely off their rockers.  I thought they had no clue what they were talking about.  Well, guess what - the reason I felt that way was because I did not have enough experience in my life to make an informed decision.  That &quot;thing inside my head&quot; was trying to process all the information that I was receiving so that I could make my own choice - but you know what?  My choice didn't matter - I was governed by the rules of my family, my school, my community, my state, and my country.  I look back in reflection and realize that they weren't far off the mark and can actually thank them for steering me away from my own stupid choices.<br>
<br>
Telling children to NOT listen to their parents.  Telling children to NOT listen to their schools.  Telling children to NOT listen to their government.  Jesus Christ, Uggmo!  What the fuck are you trying to promote?  Do you HONESTLY think that a 13 year old has enough life experience to make these adult types of decisions?<br>
<br>
Let me put it to you another way... Nature has a way of providing for itself.  You see examples in the wildlife of some species that are born with all the skills they need and their instincts guide them through life.  These animals are abandoned as infants to fend for themselves.<br>
<br>
Other species (humans included) are predisposed to remain with their young for the purposes of nurturing, providing, and teaching.  If you remove an infant from the guidance and providence of the adults of the species, not only will the child likely die from lack of sustenance, but if they do manage to survive, they will be completely at lack of the guidance to allow them to naturalize and exist successful in the environment.<br>
<br>
That is zoology 101.  That is not rocket science.<br>
<br>
Now, you are saying that children need not listen to the guiding authorities in their lives.  They have everything that they need to make their own decision.  You are plain, fucking wrong.  Take a couple of zoology, sociology, and pyschology classes sometime - or refer back to the books (if you still have them) from when you did.<br>
<br>
Again, you are pathetic in your attempts to state that drug usage is &quot;OK&quot;.  Absolutely fucking pathetic.<br>
<br>
Not only have I decided that you are an ass... you are now, in my eyes, an imbecile. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121122" > UgZug </a>
